A court has heard that there are lights near the communal toilets where Sinoxolo Mafevuka's body was discovered last year. CAPE TOWN The lawyer for one of the men accused of the rape and murder of Sinoxolo Mafevuka in Khayelitsha has questioned the lighting around the communal toilets where her body was found.The 19-year old's body was discovered in a toilet cubicle a few hundred meters from her house in SST Town Two in Khayelitsha in March last year.Cousins Xolisa and Athabile Mafilika have pleaded not guilty.WATCH: Sinoxolo Mafevuka crime scene inspectedDefence Advocate Mornay Calitz has been cross-examining SST Town Two resident Yongama Mdiya.Mdiya, who lives close to the communal toilets where Mafevuka's body was found, says he saw the body inside the toilet on the morning of 2 March 2016 while on his way to school.He has told the court he walked past the toilets the night before to buy electricity at the petrol station close by when he saw a group of about seven people standing there but was unable to identify them due to poor lighting.Calitz testified there is no light near the toilets, which is significant because another witness claims he saw the two accused drag a woman towards the toilets after midnight.(Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)